            . I am a <rs id="t18190421-37-viclabel216" type="occupation">wine merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190421-37-victim488 t18190421-37-viclabel216"></join>, in partnership with 
               <persName id="t18190421-37-person492">
                  John 
                  Burder
               <interp inst="t18190421-37-person492" type="surname" value="Burder"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-37-person492" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-37-person492" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 8th of March I marked two half crowns, and gave them to Edwards. The prisoner was our <rs id="t18190421-37-deflabel217" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190421-37-defend486 t18190421-37-deflabel217"></join>. I gave him an opportunity of going to the till, and about ten minutes called him into the counting-house. I asked him if he had any half crowns about him? he said he had none. I said I was certain he had; he then produced two, and I knew them to be the same.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-37-person493">
                  ROBERT 
                  EDWARDS
               <interp inst="t18190421-37-person493" type="surname" value="EDWARDS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-37-person493" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-37-person493" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I put the marked half crowns into the till. The prisoner came in soon after; he was called into the counting-house - he produced two, which were the same.</p>
               <p>
